<img width="2880" height="1734" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/504bf748-54b0-4fdd-998c-5a6fb6de473f" />

<img width="2880" height="1734" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ea2df83a-6cc7-4116-b571-7b34ec1fd9fe" />

<img width="2880" height="1734" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/78a1a983-7788-48b1-abaa-05ae3200a119" />

**Note**: See how patch doesn't work on the intersection which is slightly to the right of the center of the screen. The `┤` ('vertleft' fillchar) works as it is drawn at the bottom right edge of the window, but there is no `├` ('vertright' fillchar) on the similar mirrored case. If this approach would be chosen, I'd need a bit of help with making this work.

</details>
